definitions.definition: A star, especially when seen as the centre of any single solar system.
The light and warmth which is received from the sun.
Something like the sun in brightness or splendor.
Sunrise or sunset.
The nineteenth trump/major arcana card of the Tarot.
The thirty-first Lenormand card.
To expose to the warmth and radiation of the sun.
definitions.example: Beautiful bodies lying on the beach, sunning their bronzed limbs.

definitions.definition: To warm or dry in the sunshine.
To be exposed to the sun.
To expose the eyes to the sun as part of the Bates method.
The star that the Earth revolves around and from which it receives light and warmth.
A common, round fruit produced by the tree Malus domestica, cultivated in temperate climates.

Any of various tree-borne fruits or vegetables especially considered as resembling an apple; also (with qualifying words) used to form the names of other specific fruits such as custard apple, rose apple, thorn apple etc.
The fruit of the Tree of Knowledge, eaten by Adam and Eve according to post-Biblical Christian tradition; the forbidden fruit.
A tree of the genus Malus, especially one cultivated for its edible fruit; the apple tree.
The wood of the apple tree.
(in the plural) Short for apples and pears, slang for stairs.
The ball in baseball.
When smiling, the round, fleshy part of the cheeks between the eyes and the corners of the mouth.
A Native American or red-skinned person who acts and/or thinks like a white (Caucasian) person.
(ice hockey slang) An assist.
To become apple-like.
To form buds.
An incorporeal and sometimes divine messenger from a deity, or other divine entity, often depicted in art as a youthful winged figure in flowing robes.
(Abrahamic tradition) One of the lowest order of such beings, below virtues.
A person having the qualities attributed to angels, such as purity or selflessness.
definitions.example: Thanks for making me breakfast in bed, you little angel.

definitions.definition: Attendant spirit; genius; demon.
(possibly obsolete) An official (a bishop, or sometimes a minister) who heads a Christian church, especially a Catholic Apostolic church.
An English gold coin, bearing the figure of the archangel Michael, circulated between the 15th and 17th centuries, and varying in value from six shillings and eightpence to ten shillings.
(originally Royal Air Force) An altitude, measured in thousands of feet.
definitions.example: Climb to angels sixty. (“ascend to 60,000 feet”)

definitions.definition: An unidentified flying object detected by air traffic control radar.
An affluent individual who provides capital for a startup, usually in exchange for convertible debt or ownership equity; an angel investor.
The person who funds a show.
To support by donating money.
A young male.
definitions.example: Kate is dating a boy named Jim.

definitions.definition: (diminutive) A male child: a son of any age.
(diminutive) A male of any age, particularly one rather younger than the speaker.
A male of low station, (especially as pejorative) a worthless male, a wretch; a mean and dishonest male, a knave.
(now rare and usually offensive outside some Commonwealth nations) A male servant, slave, assistant, or employee, particularly:
Any non-white male, regardless of age.
A male animal, especially, in affectionate address, a male dog.
definitions.example: Are you getting a boy cat or a girl cat?

definitions.definition: A former low rank of various armed services; a holder of this rank.
Heroin.
(somewhat childish) A male (tree, gene, etc).
To use the word “boy” to refer to someone.
definitions.example: Don't boy me!

definitions.definition: To act as a boy (in allusion to the former practice of boys acting women's parts on the stage).
Exclamation of surprise, pleasure or longing.
definitions.example: Boy, I wish I could go to Canada!

definitions.definition: A female child, adolescent, or a young woman.
A young female animal.
(sometimes offensive) A woman, especially a young woman
A female servant; a maid. (see usage notes)
A queen (the playing card.)
A term of endearment. (see usage notes)
One's girlfriend.
One's daughter.
definitions.example: Your girl turned up on our doorstep.

definitions.definition: A roebuck two years old.
Cocaine, especially in powder form.
(somewhat childish) A female (tree, gene, etc).
A boy or man who is weak or sentimental.
definitions.example: Don't be such a girl!

definitions.definition: To feminize or girlify; to gender as a girl or as for girls.
(somewhat informal) To staff with or as a girl or girls.
A sheet material used for writing on or printing on (or as a non-waterproof container), usually made by draining cellulose fibres from a suspension in water.
A newspaper or anything used as such (such as a newsletter or listing magazine).
Wallpaper.
Wrapping paper.
(rock paper scissors) An open hand (a handshape resembling a sheet of paper), that beats rock and loses to scissors. It loses to lizard and beats Spock in rock-paper-scissors-lizard-Spock.
A written document, generally shorter than a book (white paper, term paper), in particular one written for the Government.

A written document that reports scientific or academic research and is usually subjected to peer review before publication in a scientific journal (as a journal article or the manuscript for one) or in the proceedings of a scientific or academic meeting (such as a conference, workshop, or symposium).
A scholastic essay.
A set of examination questions to be answered at one session.
Money.
A university course.
A paper packet containing a quantity of items.
definitions.example: a paper of pins, tacks, opium, etc.

definitions.definition: A medicinal preparation spread upon paper, intended for external application.
definitions.example: cantharides paper

definitions.definition: A substance resembling paper secreted by certain invertebrates as protection for their nests and eggs.
Free passes of admission to a theatre, etc.
(by extension) The people admitted by free passes.
To apply paper to.
definitions.example: to paper the hallway walls

definitions.definition: To document; to memorialize.
definitions.example: After they reached an agreement, their staffs papered it up.

definitions.definition: To fill (a theatre or other paid event) with complimentary seats.
definitions.example: As the event has not sold well, we'll need to paper the house.

definitions.definition: To submit official papers to (a law court, etc.).
To give public notice (typically by displaying posters) that a person is wanted by the police or other authority.
To sandpaper.
To enfold in paper.
To paste the endpapers and flyleaves at the beginning and end of a book before fitting it into its covers.
Made of paper.
definitions.example: paper bag; paper plane

definitions.definition: Insubstantial (from the weakness of common paper)
definitions.example: paper tiger; paper gangster

definitions.definition: Planned (from plans being drawn up on paper)
definitions.example: paper rocket; paper engine

definitions.definition: Having a title that is merely official, or given by courtesy or convention.
definitions.example: a paper baron; a paper lord

definitions.definition: A (generally human) male who begets a child.
definitions.example: My father was a strong influence on me.

definitions.definition: A male ancestor more remote than a parent; a progenitor; especially, a first ancestor.
A term of respectful address for an elderly man.
definitions.example: Come, father; you can sit here.

definitions.definition: A term of respectful address for a priest.
A person who plays the role of a father in some way.
definitions.example: My brother was a father to me after my parents got divorced.

definitions.definition: The founder of a discipline or science.
definitions.example: Albert Einstein is the father of modern physics.

definitions.definition: Something that is the greatest or most significant of its kind.
Something inanimate that begets.
A senator of Ancient Rome.
To be a father to; to sire.
To give rise to.
To act as a father; to support and nurture.
To provide with a father.
To adopt as one's own.
A (human) female who has given birth to a baby
definitions.example: He had something of his mother in him.

definitions.definition: A human female who parents an adopted or fostered child
A human female who donates a fertilized egg or donates a body cell which has resulted in a clone.
A pregnant female, possibly as a shortened form of mother-to-be.
definitions.example: Nutrients and oxygen obtained by the mother are conveyed to the fetus.

definitions.definition: A female parent of an animal.
definitions.example: The lioness was a mother of four cubs.

definitions.definition: A female ancestor.
A source or origin.
definitions.example: The Mediterranean was mother to many cultures and languages.

definitions.definition: Something that is the greatest or most significant of its kind. (See mother of all.)
(when followed by a surname) A title of respect for one's mother-in-law.
definitions.example: Mother Smith, meet my cousin, Doug Jones.

definitions.definition: Any elderly woman, especially within a particular community.
Any person or entity which performs mothering.
The principal piece of an astrolabe, into which the others are fixed.
The female superior or head of a religious house; an abbess, etc.
Hysterical passion; hysteria; the uterus.
A wheeled vehicle that moves independently, with at least three wheels, powered mechanically, steered by a driver and mostly for personal transportation.
definitions.example: She drove her car to the mall.

definitions.definition: A wheeled vehicle, drawn by a horse or other animal; a chariot.
An unpowered unit in a railroad train.
definitions.example: The conductor coupled the cars to the locomotive.

definitions.definition: An individual vehicle, powered or unpowered, in a multiple unit.
definitions.example: The 11:10 to London was operated by a 4-car diesel multiple unit.

definitions.definition: A passenger-carrying unit in a subway or elevated train, whether powered or not.
definitions.example: From the frontmost car of the subway, he filmed the progress through the tunnel.

definitions.definition: A rough unit of quantity approximating the amount which would fill a railroad car.
definitions.example: We ordered five hundred cars of gypsum.

definitions.definition: The moving, load-carrying component of an elevator or other cable-drawn transport mechanism.
definitions.example: Fix the car of the express elevator - the door is sticking.

definitions.definition: The passenger-carrying portion of certain amusement park rides, such as Ferris wheels.
definitions.example: The most exciting part of riding a Ferris wheel is when your car goes over the top.

definitions.definition: The part of an airship, such as a balloon or dirigible, which houses the passengers and control apparatus.
A sliding fitting that runs along a track.
The aggregate of desirable characteristics of a car.
definitions.example: Buy now! You can get more car for your money.

definitions.definition: A floating perforated box for living fish.
"Hello!" or an equivalent greeting.
To greet with "hello".
A greeting (salutation) said when meeting someone or acknowledging someone’s arrival or presence.
definitions.example: Hello, everyone.

definitions.definition: A greeting used when answering the telephone.
definitions.example: Hello? How may I help you?

definitions.definition: A call for response if it is not clear if anyone is present or listening, or if a telephone conversation may have been disconnected.
definitions.example: Hello? Is anyone there?

definitions.definition: Used sarcastically to imply that the person addressed or referred to has done something the speaker or writer considers to be foolish.
definitions.example: You just tried to start your car with your cell phone. Hello?

definitions.definition: An expression of puzzlement or discovery.
definitions.example: Hello! What’s going on here?

definitions.definition: A portal of entry into a building, room, or vehicle, consisting of a rigid plane movable on a hinge. Doors are frequently made of wood or metal. May have a handle to help open and close, a latch to hold the door closed and a lock that ensures the door cannot be opened without the key.
definitions.example: I knocked on the vice president's door

definitions.definition: Any flap, etc. that opens like a door.
definitions.example: the 24 doors in an Advent calendar

definitions.definition: (immigration) An entry point.
A means of approach or access.
definitions.example: Learning is the door to wisdom.

definitions.definition: A barrier.
definitions.example: Keep a door on your anger.

definitions.definition: A software mechanism by which a user can interact with a program running remotely on a bulletin board system. See BBS door.
To cause a collision by opening the door of a vehicle in front of an oncoming cyclist or pedestrian.
A rock; boulder; a hill.
A visible mass of water droplets suspended in the air.
Any mass of dust, steam or smoke resembling such a mass.
Anything which makes things foggy or gloomy.
Anything unsubstantial.
A dark spot on a lighter material or background.
A group or swarm, especially suspended above the ground or flying.
definitions.example: He opened the door and was greeted by a cloud of bats.

definitions.definition: An elliptical shape or symbol whose outline is a series of semicircles, supposed to resemble a cloud.
definitions.example: The comic-book character's thoughts appeared in a cloud above his head.

definitions.definition: (with "the") The Internet, regarded as an abstract amorphous omnipresent space for processing and storage, the focus of cloud computing.
A negative or foreboding aspect of something positive: see every cloud has a silver lining or every silver lining has a cloud.
Crystal methamphetamine.
A large, loosely-knitted headscarf worn by women.
To become foggy or gloomy, or obscured from sight.
definitions.example: The glass clouds when you breathe on it.

definitions.definition: To overspread or hide with a cloud or clouds.
definitions.example: The sky is clouded.

definitions.definition: To make obscure.
definitions.example: All this talk about human rights is clouding the real issue.

definitions.definition: To make less acute or perceptive.
definitions.example: The tears began to well up and cloud my vision.

definitions.definition: To make gloomy or sullen.
To blacken; to sully; to stain; to tarnish (reputation or character).
To mark with, or darken in, veins or sports; to variegate with colors.
definitions.example: to cloud yarn

definitions.definition: To become marked, darkened or variegated in this way.
Son of the same parents as another person.
A male having at least one parent in common with another (see half-brother, stepbrother).
A male fellow member of a religious community, church, trades union etc.
definitions.example: I would like to thank the brother who just spoke.

definitions.definition: A form of address to a man.
definitions.example: Listen, brother, I don't know what you want, but I'm not interested.

definitions.definition: A black male.
Somebody, usually male, connected by a common cause or situation.
Someone who is a peer, whether male or female.
To treat as a brother.
Expressing exasperation.
definitions.example: We're being forced to work overtime? Oh, brother!

definitions.definition: A daughter of the same parents as another person; a female sibling.
definitions.example: My sister is always driving me crazy.

definitions.definition: A female member of a religious order; especially one devoted to more active service; (informally) a nun.
definitions.example: Michelle left behind her bank job and became a sister at the local convent.

definitions.definition: Any butterfly in the genus Adelpha, so named for the resemblance of the dark-colored wings to the black habit traditionally worn by nuns.
A senior or supervisory nurse, often in a hospital.
Any woman or girl with whom a bond is felt through common membership of a race, profession, religion or organization, such as feminism.
definitions.example: Connie was very close to her friend Judy and considered her to be her sister.

definitions.definition: (sometimes capitalized) A black woman.
A form of address to a woman.
definitions.example: What’s up, sister?

definitions.definition: A woman, in certain labour or socialist circles; also as a form of address.
definitions.example: Thank you, sister. I would like to thank the sister who just spoke.

definitions.definition: An entity that has a special or affectionate, non-hierarchical relationship with another.
definitions.example: sister city

definitions.definition: A node in a data structure that shares its parent with another node.
(usually attributively) Something in the same class.
definitions.example: sister facility

definitions.definition: To strengthen (a supporting beam) by fastening a second beam alongside it.
definitions.example: I’m trying to correct my sagging floor by sistering the joists.

definitions.definition: To be sister to; to resemble closely.
A stringed musical instrument, of European origin, usually with a fretted fingerboard and six strings, played with the fingers or a plectrum (guitar pick).

Any type of musical instrument of the lute family, characterized by a flat back, along with a neck whose upper surface is in the same plane as the soundboard, with strings along the neck and parallel to the soundboard.
To play the guitar.
